---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import Section from '../components/Section.astro';
import BottomCTA from '../components/BottomCTA.astro';
import Button from '../components/Button.astro';

const homeSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'ProfessionalService',
  name: 'Signal to Summit',
  description: 'Strategic advisory for retail media platform leaders. Helping technically strong platforms stop losing deals they should win.',
  url: 'https://signaltosummit.com',
  areaServed: 'US',
  serviceType: 'Strategic Advisory',
  founder: {
    '@type': 'Person',
    name: 'Jaiah Kamara',
    jobTitle: 'Founder',
  },
  hasOfferCatalog: {
    '@type': 'OfferCatalog',
    name: 'Advisory Services',
    itemListElement: [
      { '@type': 'Offer', itemOffered: { '@type': 'Service', name: 'Executive Briefing', description: 'A session on the patterns that stall retail media deals, tailored to your specific market position.' } },
      { '@type': 'Offer', itemOffered: { '@type': 'Service', name: 'Strategy Review', description: 'A focused diagnosis of your retail media strategy, go-to-market execution, or implementation.' } },
      { '@type': 'Offer', itemOffered: { '@type': 'Service', name: 'Readiness Assessment', description: 'A two-part diagnostic that maps what is impacting adoption inside your retailer customers.' } },
      { '@type': 'Offer', itemOffered: { '@type': 'Service', name: 'Strategic Advisory', description: 'Ongoing access to operator-level judgment through scheduled sessions and on-demand advisory.' } },
    ],
  },
};
---

<PageLayout
  title="Signal to Summit"
  description="Strategic advisory for platform leaders navigating retail media — where the gap between what you've built and how retailers actually operate determines whether you win."
  schema={homeSchema}
>
  {/* ── Section 1.1: HERO ── */}
  <div class="bg-white p-4 md:p-6">
    <section class="relative h-[78vh] md:h-[80vh] flex items-center overflow-hidden">
      {/* Background image with dark overlay */}
      <img
        src="/images/hero-mountain-original.jpg"
        alt=""
        class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover object-[center_22%]"
        loading="eager"
        decoding="async"
      />
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-summit-navy/70"></div>
      <div class="relative mx-auto w-full max-w-[45rem] px-6">
        <h1 class="text-white text-[1.75rem] md:text-[2rem] font-bold leading-[1.3] tracking-[-0.02em] mb-6">
          Your product isn't the problem. The way it meets the retailer's operating reality is.
        </h1>
        <p class="text-white/80 text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed mb-10 max-w-2xl">
          Strategic advisory for platform leaders navigating retail media — where the gap between what you've built and how retailers actually operate determines whether you win.
        </p>
        <Button href="/lets-talk">Let's Talk</Button>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

  {/* ── Section 1.2: PROBLEM RECOGNITION ── */}
  <Section>
    <h2 class="text-summit-navy mb-8">You've seen this pattern before.</h2>

    <div class="space-y-12">
      {/* Block 1 — Coalition Dynamics */}
      <div>
        <p class="text-signal-blue-dark text-base font-bold tracking-wide uppercase mb-4">Coalition Dynamics</p>
        <p class="text-summit-navy/90 leading-relaxed">
          The retail media lead is aligned. The demo went well. But the deal stalls anyway — because the champion who said yes isn't the person who controls implementation priority, data access, or budget. Deals don't die from product gaps. They die from coalition misalignment your team never mapped.
        </p>
      </div>

      {/* Block 2 — Delivery Scaling */}
      <div>
        <p class="text-signal-blue-dark text-base font-bold tracking-wide uppercase mb-4">Delivery Scaling</p>
        <p class="text-summit-navy/90 leading-relaxed">
          Your first implementations required heroes. Now every new customer requires the same heroics. Revenue grows linearly with headcount. That's not a scaling challenge — it's a ceiling.
        </p>
      </div>

      {/* Block 3 — Absorption Capacity */}
      <div>
        <p class="text-signal-blue-dark text-base font-bold tracking-wide uppercase mb-4">Absorption Capacity</p>
        <p class="text-summit-navy/90 leading-relaxed">
          The retailer says they're interested but nothing moves. It's not a priority problem. The organization is operating under constraints your team consistently underestimates — bandwidth, data readiness, process maturity. The limiting factor isn't what they agreed to buy — it's what your approach assumed they could absorb without support.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  {/* ── Section 1.3: VANTAGE POINT ── */}
  <Section background="soft-gray">
    <h2 class="text-summit-navy mb-8">Diagnosed from the inside, not studied from the outside.</h2>

    <p class="text-summit-navy/90 leading-relaxed">
      Seven years inside a top-10 U.S. retail media network. The patterns that stall platform deals — coalition misalignment, delivery scaling, absorption capacity — were diagnosed from the operator's chair, not a conference stage.
    </p>
  </Section>

  {/* ── Section 1.4: THESIS VIDEO FEATURE ── */}
  <Section>
    <h2 class="text-summit-navy mb-2">Why Retail Media Deals Fall Apart — and What to Do About It</h2>
    <p class="text-summit-navy/70 text-base md:text-lg mb-8">
      Why technically strong platforms lose deals they should win.
    </p>

    <div class="aspect-video rounded-lg overflow-hidden mb-6">
      <iframe
        src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/r9kU32Wl6Aw?rel=0"
        title="The Real Challenge in Retail Media — Signal to Summit"
        class="w-full h-full"
        frameborder="0"
        allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture"
        allowfullscreen
        loading="lazy"
      ></iframe>
    </div>

    <a href="/summit-signals/why-retail-media-deals-fall-apart" class="text-signal-blue-dark hover:text-signal-blue font-medium transition-colors">
      Read the full thesis &rarr;
    </a>
  </Section>

  {/* ── Section 1.5: SERVICES PREVIEW ── */}
  <Section>
    <h2 class="text-summit-navy mb-10">How we work together.</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6 md:space-y-0 md:grid md:grid-cols-2 md:gap-8">
      {/* Card 1 — Executive Briefing */}
      <div class="border border-soft-gray rounded-lg p-6 md:p-8 hover:border-signal-blue/30 transition-colors">
        <p class="text-summit-navy font-bold text-lg mb-2">Executive Briefing</p>
        <p class="text-summit-navy/80 italic text-base mb-4">
          "What am I missing about how retail media actually operates?"
        </p>
        <a href="/services" class="text-signal-blue-dark hover:text-signal-blue font-semibold text-sm transition-colors">
          Learn more &rarr;
        </a>
      </div>

      {/* Card 2 — Strategy Review */}
      <div class="border border-soft-gray rounded-lg p-6 md:p-8 hover:border-signal-blue/30 transition-colors">
        <p class="text-summit-navy font-bold text-lg mb-2">Strategy Review</p>
        <p class="text-summit-navy/80 italic text-base mb-4">
          "Are we reading the situation correctly?"
        </p>
        <a href="/services" class="text-signal-blue-dark hover:text-signal-blue font-semibold text-sm transition-colors">
          Learn more &rarr;
        </a>
      </div>

      {/* Card 3 — Readiness Assessment */}
      <div class="border border-soft-gray rounded-lg p-6 md:p-8 hover:border-signal-blue/30 transition-colors">
        <p class="text-summit-navy font-bold text-lg mb-2">Readiness Assessment</p>
        <p class="text-summit-navy/80 italic text-base mb-4">
          "Where is the friction in our implementation?"
        </p>
        <a href="/services" class="text-signal-blue-dark hover:text-signal-blue font-semibold text-sm transition-colors">
          Learn more &rarr;
        </a>
      </div>

      {/* Card 4 — Strategic Advisory */}
      <div class="border border-soft-gray rounded-lg p-6 md:p-8 hover:border-signal-blue/30 transition-colors">
        <p class="text-summit-navy font-bold text-lg mb-2">Strategic Advisory</p>
        <p class="text-summit-navy/80 italic text-base mb-4">
          "Do I have the right thinking partner for what's ahead?"
        </p>
        <a href="/services" class="text-signal-blue-dark hover:text-signal-blue font-semibold text-sm transition-colors">
          Learn more &rarr;
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  {/* ── Section 1.6: BOTTOM CTA ── */}
  <BottomCTA heading="If this sounds like what you're navigating, let's talk." />
</PageLayout>
